post_text: There just aren’t enough thank yous to properly let Susan Walker, Cheyanna Lambert, Diane Clements, and Barb Zelhart know how grateful the band program is for their efforts sewing 119 horn covers for the students to help them stay healthy during this pandemic. Thank you also to Amie Zimmerman-Stadtmueller and Lisa Oswald for helping thread some elastic.
text: There just aren’t enough thank yous to properly let Susan Walker, Cheyanna Lambert, Diane Clements, and Barb Zelhart know how grateful the band program is for their efforts sewing 119 horn covers for the students to help them stay healthy during this pandemic. Thank you also to Amie Zimmerman-Stadtmueller and Lisa Oswald for helping thread some elastic.

post_text: First of a couple of shout outs this week: Earlier this week the band directors reached out to the Fine Arts Boosters (formerly the Band Parents and Treble Makers) about some help with horn covers to help limit the spread of germs. An all-call was put out and many talented hands reached out. Today’s shout out goes to Susan Walker (Miss Walker’s mother) for sewing 35 covers (that’s love) and to this crew for cutting fabric and elastic this afternoon for the other 80-some instruments. A special thank-you to Shirley Stadtmueller for donating elastic.

shared_text:
JAZZHOUSTON.ORG
ONLINE SESSION REGISTRATION — Jazz Houston

Vincent Gardner
April 14 at 1:16 AM ·

CALLING ALL YOUNG IMPROVISERS!! I’ll be teaching the following FREE online classes this week. We’ve been having a great time over the last two weeks, so parents/educators, if you have students that want to keep their chops up during the break, send them to the link below to register!

Wednesday April 15
1:00 P.M. CST - Beginning Improvisation Level 1
3:00 P.M. CST - Beginning Improvisation Level 2

Thursday April 16
12:00 P.M. CST - Transcription Level 1
4:00 P.M. CST - Transcription Level 2 - You MUST attend level 1 in order to participate!

Friday April 17
1:00 P.M. CST - Bebop vs. Hard Bop...they are NOT the same thing!! This is a non-playing Listening and Discussion class ONLY. The class will be broadcast live on Jazz Houston’s Facebook page.

Register using the link below!

The jazz band earned a Division I rating at the IHSMA state jazz festival, but the season is nowhere over! The students rehearse Mondays, Tuesdays, and Thursdays before school, and they've got some big events coming up!
Thursday, Feb. 20: Tallcorn Jazz Festival at UNI
Thursday, Feb. 27: MS and HS jazz concert at the high school at 7pm. Add it to your calendar!
Friday, Feb. 28: Jazz Summit at Coe College
Saturday, March 7: NEIBA jazz competition at Independence High School

post_text: The marching band earned a Division II rating at the IHSMA State contest this morning at Kingston Stadium in Cedar Rapids. The band moved up to 3A this year, and it was 2.5 points from a I rating. This band is blessed with some seasoned leaders and lots of young talent along with a vocal fan club! Next year the band should (hopefully) have an established practice field once the construction is finished. Thanks for a great marching season, Panthers!
